## ColorBlock

**Path**: `@/components/ColorBlock`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → color-blocks (509:2598), color filters (512:3142).

24×24 color swatch with optional label below. When `label` is set: column layout, 8px gap, 8px padding, label = medium/paragraph-sm (14px, #1E201E). **Selected**: 2px inner border #101828, 2px radius. **Colors**: white, red, green (default), black, silver, yellow, blue.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `color` | `ColorBlockColor` | No | `"white"` \| `"red"` \| `"green"` \| `"black"` \| `"silver"` \| `"yellow"` \| `"blue"` (default `"green"`) |
| `label` | `string` | No | When set, show label below block (color filters style) |
| `selected` | `boolean` | No | Show selection ring (default false) |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the root wrapper |

**Exports**: `ColorBlock`, `ColorBlockColor`, `ColorBlockProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { ColorBlock } from "@/components/ColorBlock";

<ColorBlock color="green" />
<ColorBlock color="red" label="Red" selected />
<ColorBlock label="Green" />
```

